<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-677-243  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 677 243.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Dec 10 1990 v36 n1839 p3(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>System Industries settles suit by DEC, will phase out line. (suitover data/tape patent infringement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lapedus, Mark.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>System Industries Inc agrees out of court to settle apatent-infringement suit by paying DEC an undisclosed sum anddiscontinuing its C series of disk and tape drive subsystems.andP;  DECfiled the suit in April 1990, charging System Industries withviolating four DEC patents covering disk-interconnect technology.andO;Milpitas, CA-based System Industries garners two-fifths of itstotal sales from the C series.andP;  System Industries will continue tosell the C series products for an unspecified length of time.andP;  TheC series includes 8-mm and 3480 compatible tape drives as well as5.25-inch and 8-inch storage controllers.andP;  As part of thesettlement, DEC will license its VAXBI and Turbo channel bustechnologies to System Industries.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Equipment Corp. (Cases)System Industries Inc. (Cases).andO;Ticker:    SYI; DEC.andO;Topic:     Law SuitProduct DiscontinuationPatentDisk DrivesTape DrivesContracts.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>